snippet.textDisplay:
0:33 - that Demi represents a dark time of her life, ‘here we go again’ and emo era

0:43 - that Demi is wearing her gym brand ‘fabletics’ and makes a reference to those times when she was obsessed with working out

1:42 - her mom, Dianna, is looking for a job after Demi’s father left, and holding Demi and Dallas’ hands too

1:46 - that woman standing with stripes on her pants references Demi’s ex best friend, Marissa, who also left her in a bad time of her life

1:55 - confident era, also Demi is being surrounded by guards and people who subliminally controlled her

1:57 - camp rock (a really important part of her past)

2:09 - those are the jonas brothers. Demi is no longer friends with them bc they abandoned her after the OD. they are also wearing the outfits they wore at the grammys

3:01 - Demi references her OD back in 2018, almost like she’s saying goodbye to that version of her

3:06 - Wilmer Valderrama, Demi’s ex, walks hand in hand with his new fiancé, and she sadly stares at them

3:16 - Matthew and Sirah, Demi’s best friends, and they’ve been with her and supporting her since always

snippet.textDisplay:
I cannot express how disappointed I am because absolutely everything that says in that song I can identify with my life. I really understand, because I'm the same thing. And most people do not understand how difficult it is to have self-esteem on the ground, not being able to understand and literally being always in conflict with yourself. It is mentally exhausting. I'm sorry for all the people out there that like her and like me we have to go through feelings like this, and all the damage we do ourselves unconsciously.
Maybe today it's a Sunny day for her, but usually Shadows come back. I hope she Stay Strong.
